{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.5",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 5 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:1",
      "text": "Call now, if there be any that will answer thee; and to which of the saints wilt thou turn?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:2",
      "text": "For wrath killeth the foolish man, and envy slayeth the silly one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:3",
      "text": "I have seen the foolish taking root: but suddenly I cursed his habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:4",
      "text": "His children are far from safety, and they are crushed in the gate, neither is there any to deliver them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:5",
      "text": "Whose harvest the hungry eateth up, and taketh it even out of the thorns, and the robber swalloweth up their substance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:6",
      "text": "Although affliction cometh not forth of the dust, neither doth trouble spring out of the ground;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:7",
      "text": "Yet man is born unto trouble, as the sparks fly upward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:8",
      "text": "I would seek unto God, and unto God would I commit my cause:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:9",
      "text": "Which doeth great things and unsearchable; marvellous things without number:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:10",
      "text": "Who giveth rain upon the earth, and sendeth waters upon the fields:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:11",
      "text": "To set up on high those that be low; that those which mourn may be exalted to safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:12",
      "text": "He disappointeth the devices of the crafty, so that their hands cannot perform their enterprise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:13",
      "text": "He taketh the wise in their own craftiness: and the counsel of the froward is carried headlong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:14",
      "text": "They meet with darkness in the daytime, and grope in the noonday as in the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:15",
      "text": "But he saveth the poor from the sword, from their mouth, and from the hand of the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:16",
      "text": "So the poor hath hope, and iniquity stoppeth her mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:17",
      "text": "Behold, happy is the man whom God correcteth: therefore despise not thou the chastening of the Almighty:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:18",
      "text": "For he maketh sore, and bindeth up: he woundeth, and his hands make whole.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:19",
      "text": "He shall deliver thee in six troubles: yea, in seven there shall no evil touch thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:20",
      "text": "In famine he shall redeem thee from death: and in war from the power of the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:21",
      "text": "Thou shalt be hid from the scourge of the tongue: neither shalt thou be afraid of destruction when it cometh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:22",
      "text": "At destruction and famine thou shalt laugh: neither shalt thou be afraid of the beasts of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:23",
      "text": "For thou shalt be in league with the stones of the field: and the beasts of the field shall be at peace with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:24",
      "text": "And thou shalt know that thy tabernacle shall be in peace; and thou shalt visit thy habitation, and shalt not sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:25",
      "text": "Thou shalt know also that thy seed shall be great, and thine offspring as the grass of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:26",
      "text": "Thou shalt come to thy grave in a full age, like as a shock of corn cometh in in his season.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.5.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:27",
      "text": "Lo this, we have searched it, so it is; hear it, and know thou it for thy good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
